caption: Great place to eat and awesome food! Found it a few weeks back and will be a usual.

Prices just went up by 25%. I was surprised since the menu still has their old prices but they have TVs with new menus. I understand restaurants are struggling but this place has always been takeout only. Sad to say my favorite place will no longer be my go to for quick healthy meals.
Yummy food and fast service
Used to be real good. The portions have  decreased dramatically.
Toasted, dry shawarmas

Got hit with a craving for mediterranean food so I rolled up here as I heard a lot of good things about this place. Place was popping, always people in there getting take out. Lemme just first say the food is so cheap and they give you so much! 8$ get you a plate of shawarma packed full, rice, hummus, salad, and pita. Definitely will fill you up.  I got the meat combo but just asked for lamb and the kefta. Food was good for the price. Lamb shawarma was great, flavorful not tough but I wouldn't say it was tender either. The kefta was a little dry but still not bad. Same with the rice, a little mushy for my liking and the pita was kinda hard. Like not stale but like they just took it out of the bag, I wish they heated it up a little. Hummus a great though, smooth, not as smooth as Aba but it was solid.  For the price, you can't beat this, a very good deal.

One of my favorite falafel places in the city!! The vegetarian combo is such a good deal—tons of food for $7. The falafel and lentil soup is perfect. The only thing it could use is some pickles on top.
The people here are so kind and always give a warm greeting. The prices and amount of food they give you cant compare to any other place. You'll always have leftovers or a feast 😋
As close to European shawarma as I could find in Chicago. Finally. Love it, and cheap. Can't go wrong. The lamb is also real lamb, not formed meat goop (gyros).
Delicious and a great value!
Relaxed, casual place with decent food.
Great service. Great food. Try their pomengrenate mollases too.
Tried chicken shawarma plate ... it was so good and tender...
Great comforting food. The chicken soup is a must try!

Tasty, quick, and cheap are there words that come to mind whenever I think of Sultan’s Market. The portions are huge and the meat is very flavorful. The hummus was excellent and the pita bread as well as the rice and beans were both on par. Also would recommend the lentil soup which was nice thick - perfect for a winter dinner.

Sultan's Market is my go-to, quick Mediterranean food restaurant in the city. The food is delicious and the price is very reasonable for the amount of food you get. I've only ordered take out so I am not sure what it would be like to eat inside. I love their meat combo dinner, and I always compliment it with some lentil soup as well. Hits the spot everytime!
Cheap prices and quality food! Can't beat!
middle eastern food, super good. i think i might become a regular.
Best bang for your buck. Such a great shawarma plate with the lentil rice and tabbouleh! YUM!
One of the best shawarma places.
Middle Eastern food, super delicious. Very filling. Prices that won't shock you.
Quality food Reason able price fast service
Poor quality! Not fresh at all! Not recommended. Don't even know how come there is high rate! People must've not experienced a high quality Mediterranean Food before

Always super solid! Been grabbing sultan's for the last five years and haven't had a single bad experience. Consistency is key and this place is it. Prices and portion size is fantastic for the city and they never skimp on size. The food itself has a ton of flavor and is delicious. I always order the combination plate, lentil soup and baklava. Keep it up sultan's!
Middle Eastern food and the feeling at this spot is very good. I was so full. Service treated us so kindly.
middle eastern food and service at this spot is excellent. The service here is outstanding. Food and atmosphere reminds me of Atlanta.
One of the best bang for you buck dinner meals in the city if you want large potions. I recommend the lamb shawarma!
I’ve ordered the dinner combo both times- great tasting food for a good price!
Spicy pita sandwiches are 🔥🔥🔥

Highly recommend their baked meat pie(I don’t know what kind of heavenly species did they used just try it!) and Hummus. I gave 4 star because of the Hummus and meat pie but their food quality is somewhere around 3. Considering the large portion and low price and their fabulous meat pie I gave them a 4. The Kefte kabob, Shawarma and curry basmati rice was good but I don’t recommend their lentil rice and their Baba Ganuj(one of the worst I ever had) but you have a lot of other options to try. The portion was so big that both me and my wife was full after finishing one together.

If you plan to go to some fast food chain near here, shame on you. Sultan’s Market is the beat deal in Lincoln Park/Lakeview area. Always fresh, always friendly staff that hook up great portions and are willing to accommodate your order. Hummus high quality, two different rice options are nice and they have a badass salad bar. Hit em up!
Love the food here. Meat is tender and juicy. The rice flavorful. As a meat lover I seem to prefer their falafel which is weird for me but that’s just how good it is. 10/10 must try
Very great place for middle eastern food One of the best falafel sandwiches.
Awesome place
Solid falafel, get the vegetarian plate!
Food not too top

I don't know how they manage to knock nearly everything they make out of the park but they somehow do it. I challenge you to find a more breathtakingly fresh and beautiful salad bar (when they have it, no salad bar during the pandemic). The egg pie is just pita, egg, and cheese yet it's one of my favorite foods on the planet. The super tasty seasoned beef pie, schwarma sandwich, and falafel are all regular orders of mine. Along with Taza in the Loop, they fry up some of the best falafel in town.

Easily best Middle Eastern option my neck of woods in Lincoln Park. Small, compact menu of standard fares - excellent Falafels, & Schwarmas in sandwich/pita form and dinners. Easy take out pick up in our current days of Covid-19 environment.

The meat combo is enough for 2 people. Lots of meat and lots of flavor. Food was made extremely quickly as well. I’ve tried lots of Mediterranean places, and I definitely think Sultan’s Market is one of the better tasting restaurants.

This is one of my favorite places to get food. There hummus is really good. I recommend this place. If you are in town or looking for a good place to eat. I highly recommend stopping at this place and get some of there amazing wonderful tasty food.

Popular restaurant with prompt service. The food has depth in taste, multiple textures, and moderately priced. There isn't much seating. Most people take food to go. Don't let the size or plain decor stop you from stopping and enjoying this fine food.

Affordable sandwiches, baked pies, plates and salad bar for dine-in, take out or delivery. I love the falafel sandwich with feta added and extra spicy! A nice assortment of canned and bottled drinks to choose from and baklava or Turkish Delight for dessert. You can eat well for $6-10.

I frequent this place very often l probably have been here over 50 60 time it has the best falafel in Chicago par none I am a certified falafel guru I know my falafel and this place has great falafel just go go go and enjoy yourself

middle eastern food, mmm, super delicious. service is always awesome even when they have a full house. i've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting. the place has a good atmosphere. feels similar to a restaurant in new york i loved.

Hands down the best Middle Eastern food you can find in the city. I have yet to try somewhere that tops it, and even if I ever do the price will not be beat. Sultan's Market is GREAT food for a GREAT price. Huge portions in a hole-in-the-wall setting. What's not to like?

It's small so might be hard to find a spot to eat in, luckily there's a park a few blocks over, great for a picnic on a nice day outside.

We had chicken shawrma, and it was AMAZING! We don't mind to drive back from Milwaukee to Chicago to have it again. The staff were awesome, Peter is a wonderful man. Very friendly and elegant. The cook was very helpful with offering samples. Great place. Thank you!

Authentic Mediterranean with amazing quality and value! It's easy to miss this hidden gem on Clark Street's endless number of great restaurants, but it's worth stopping in. It's not a typical  restaurant or fast food joint, but a hidden gem. We went there after a friend's recommendation, and were not disappointed. The owner/staff were friendly. There is a wonderful salad bar to spoil you for choices , and one of the best falafals, schwarma you would have ever tasted. The only negative point you would think of is the amount of space it has for dine in. But like I said, gems don't come with typical space rooms. I am not sure if they take online orders ( probably they do via GrubHub or something) but have heard their takeaway is the main contribution for most of the foot traffic here. Go enjoy , that's enough to make your mind , you hungry looking, confused soul who would take breath of life after reading reviews of the air around..just kidding it's a nice place to try out.
Vegan friendly place! Food is good and easy on the pocket!

This was a very nice place to stop for dinner while my husband and I were traveling. The gentlemen working let us try a few samples to help us decide what to order. Every Halloween, we are here on Mission Street with sweets for trick-or-treaters...then, dinner at Old Jerusalem - our 8th Halloween  to enjoy the good food and friendly service. Meat Combo with hummus, pita, and Kunafe.  Delicious!

Delicious, fast, and cheap. Couldn't ask for a better lunch spot. I stop in every week and usually load up a bowl with salad fixings and then ask them to add falafel or shawarma. We've been ordering lunch at work from their North Ave location for years and I finally go a chance to stop in at this one on Clark and I couldn't have been happier. The staff was courteous and helpful and the food was just as I have come to expect- Cheap, plentiful, and full of flavor! This is my favorite shop in the area. When I work at our clark satellite I ALWAYS eat here. I used to get the lamb or chicken sandwich. Then i went vegetarian and thought I would no longer like it, but was willing to give the falafel sandwich and I'm a believer. Its the best falafel I've ever had. Did I mention that it is cheap too? Yeah, if you like this kind of food this is the best bang for your buck. I now believe world peace is possible.

Amazing food and quality for how afordable it is. Very laid back and relaxed environment. My go to selections are the falafel sandwhich, lentil soup, and their rice. Delicious and low priced schwarma. Will be back again soon!
This place was a real surprise. Great, quick food at great prices. Small with little seating but the food was great.

The food wasn't bad, but I think it could have used something more.  Maybe I just ordered the wrong thing.  I got a lamb sandwich and I was craving some sort of sauce on it.  The felafel was really light and tasty.
Awesome place! Good food, great price lovely staff

If I had one of these near my place I'd probably stop in for the buffet at least once a day.  Cash only, which is kind of annoying, but great variety of meats, veggies, sauces, and more.  Awesome spot for vegetarians and gulten freers.
Quick, cheap, delicious. If I'm in the area and hungry I definitely make a point of stopping by. The portion sizes are also great. It's a little small so I generally take it to go.
Super healthy tasting food. Lentil soup is like no other.

Sultan Market is the best when it comes to Middle Eastern food. A great addition to Lincoln Park. Their chicken dinner plate is so flavorful and their hummus is out f this world. Have been here for over a year now.

As someone who grew up eating middle eastern food this place has good quality food. I had the Combo meat plate, the chicken was ok, the rice was really good, the tabuli salad was phenomenal, the meet was flavorful but a bit dry. I like the self serve style where you can just grab your own to-go container and other things, but the fact that water is in a nasty looking container which is luke warm and no other option is provided irritated me. oh and the falafel was really good as well. I guess my review is mixed but all I could give was 3 stars because of the things i pointed out that were lacking.
Get a falafel sandwich for $4. It's enough food for two meals and fabulous. They put hummus and tabouleh salad in the sandwiches without having to pay extra too!

This spot is legit! First of all the food is the best thing you can get under $5! Ay but what's even doper is that the staff is the BOMB! I usually get that good falafel sandwich nawsaying...spicy always because that's how a real G rolls. I usually pair that with a nice Aloe water like a BOSS beacuse I keep it healthy. Don't sleep on the salad bar b...get up on those grape leave joints and if you like eating meat go ahead and smash those chicken shiwarmas! BOOM!
The best service ever. The dudes working here always put a smile on my face. Also, best value healthy meal around- the falafel is unmatched and the grape leaves are great too.
Get the lentils and the rice! It's only 3 dollars and so delicious. There has never been a wait everytime I go and the dudes who work there are nice as hell.
Cheap place to eat with great tasting food
Albeit small it's cozy and has a great selection of middle eastern food that is served fast and if you like spicy and tasty food you have to try it out at least once, it's shawarma is great,
love the salad bar! where else can you get roasted Brussels sprouts baba ganesh hummus Kalamata olives and a pita for $5? great. place!

I love this place fast food fresh! The spicy falafel is by far my favorite! On a cold miserable day the lentil soup makes you feel all warm and satisfied! fyi add some rice to the bottom for that I just ate at grandma's house feeling! P.S. try the butterscotch cookies they are vegan and good!

The Lincoln Park outpost to North Avenue's original is tiny (don't plan on eating in house), but their falafel balls are just as delicious and they have the same offerings, albeit a smaller salad bar. The parking sitch is just the same though. Do yourself a favor and take the bus.
Best middle eastern food outside the middle east! Authentic!
